HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1425
By Reneau
A RESOLUTION to honor the firefighters of the State of
Tennessee for their contributions to public
safety.
WHEREAS, fire service is a core public safety function, alongside law enforcement and
emergency medical services; and
WHEREAS, firefighters, both career and volunteer, respond to a wide range of
emergencies, including structure fires, vehicle accidents, medical calls, and natural disasters;
and
WHEREAS, fire departments play a vital role in protecting life, property, and the safety of
our communities; and
WHEREAS, many areas of the State rely heavily on volunteer fire departments, whose
members often serve at great personal sacrifice and with limited resources; and
WHEREAS, it is important that fire services are supported and recognized for their
contributions to public safety and community well-being; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby honor the firefighters of the State of Tennessee and commend
them for the critical role they play in protecting our communities across the Volunteer State.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
